  - [Does it snow in Moab?](https://www.undercanvas.com/camps/moab/#)
  
  
  Moab experiences some seasonal variation and occasional snowfall, particularly in the higher elevations. The snowiest months tend to be December and January, which average approximately three to five inches per month. Under Canvas Moab is open from March – October.
  
  - [What is Moab known for?](https://www.undercanvas.com/camps/moab/#)
  
  
  Moab is at the heart of Utah’s Canyon Country. It is home to two national parks, the Colorado River, and thousands of square miles of public lands brimming with outdoor adventures and breathtaking beauty.
  
  - [How far is Canyonlands National Park from Moab?](https://www.undercanvas.com/camps/moab/#)
  
  
  Canyonlands National Park is 30 minutes from the town of Moab. Under Canvas Moab is located 25 minutes from the Island in the Sky entrance to Canyonlands National Park.
  
  - [How far is Arches National Park from Moab?](https://www.undercanvas.com/camps/moab/#)
  
  
  Arches National Park is 10 minutes from the town of Moab. Under Canvas Moab is located 12 minutes from the entrance to Arches National Park.
  
  
